"v.饮；吸入 【英】 v. 饮(to drink)；吸入(to absorb) 【记】 im(进入)+bibe(=drin k 喝)→喝入 【例】 a sponge imbibes moisture v. 饮; 吸入 = absorb; 摄取(接收或吸收到脑中) 【记】im进入, bibe喝－喝入－吸收 【参】pipe(n 管子; 输送管)用pipe吸水－吸收 【类】thirsty: imbibe = exhausted: rest 渴所以喝水 = 疲惫的所以休息 【记】im, in + bib 吸水；in + baby 小baby整天只知道吸入，吸奶，吸果汁等；音：饮杯杯，饮水杯 【相关】bibulous 饮酒的,吸水的 imbibe (v.)  late 14c., from Old French imbiber, embiber ""to soak into,"" from Latin imbibere ""absorb, drink in, inhale,"" from assimilated form of in- ""into, in, on, upon"" (see in- (2)) + bibere ""to drink,"" related to potare ""to drink,"" from PIE *po(i)- ""to drink"" (see potion). Figurative sense of ""mentally drink in"" (knowledge, ideas, etc.) was the main one in classical Latin, first attested in English 1550s. Related: Imbibed; imbibing."
